Jarvis is an autonomous "Active Defense" agent designed to proactively detect and neutralize network threats in real-time. Built with Python, it operates as a modular system where the Monitor sniffs live packets and maps them to local processes, the Detector cross-references traffic against global threat intelligence feeds (like Tor Exit Nodes), and the Firewall orchestrates OS-level blocks (via netsh or iptables) to sever malicious connections instantly. Featuring a built-in honeypot for decoy detection and multi-threaded architecture, Jarvis serves as an educational framework for understanding how automated Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) tools defend against modern cyberattacksâ€”use with caution, as it actively modifies system firewall rules.
